{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846341671,"sessionID":"ses_28752efdeffeMucK6tRnSSb4lm","part":{"id":"prt_d78b0bb74001ssMuxIJH66fcW5","messageID":"msg_d78ad79780014RIpceVvZ4wZ1U","sessionID":"ses_28752efdeffeMucK6tRnSSb4lm","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-de5297c32dde4cb99db329385e37de5e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-007 Implementation Plan\n\n**Feature:** AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器\n**Goal:** Implement Kubernetes-native reconciler controllers for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs using controller-runtime to provide automated lifecycle management for sandbox resources with proper event handling and status reporting.\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- AgentRuntimeReconciler successfully creates and manages sandbox resources\n- CodeInterpreterReconciler successfully creates and manages sandbox resources\n- Status conditions are accurately updated during reconciliation (Ready, Error, Progressing, etc.)\n- Finalizers are properly handled for resource deletion\n- Events are recorded for all significant operations\n- Metrics are exposed and can be scraped by Prometheus\n- Unit tests cover all major code paths\n- Integration tests validate end-to-end reconciliation\n- Error handling is robust and provides clear feedback\n- Reconciler can handle spec changes gracefully\n- Leader election works correctly in HA deployments\n**Architecture:** Controller-runtime based reconciler pattern with separate reconcilers for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs, coexisting with existing HTTP-based controller, using agent-sandbox API for sandbox lifecycle management.\n**Tech Stack:** Go, controller-runtime, client-go, agent-sandbox API, Prometheus metrics, Ginkgo/Gomega testing\n**前端验证:** No\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Create reconciler package directory structure\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/`\n\n**Step 1: Create reconciler directory**\n\n```bash\nmkdir -p pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler\n```\n\n**Step 2: Verify directory created**\n\nRun: `ls -la pkg/workloadmanager/controller/`\nExpected: Output shows reconciler/ directory\n\n**Step 3: Create package documentation file**\n\n```go\n// Package reconciler implements Kubernetes reconciler controllers for\n// AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs using controller-runtime.\n//\n// The reconcilers watch for changes to CRDs and automatically manage\n// the lifecycle of associated sandbox resources.\npackage reconciler\n```\n\n**Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/doc.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(ar-007): create reconciler package structure\"\n```\n\n### Task 2: Define reconciler types and interfaces\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/types.go`\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\n```go\n// pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/types_test.go\npackage reconciler\n\nimport (\n\t\"testing\"\n\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n\tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/types\"\n\tctrl \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime\"\n)\n\nfunc TestReconcilerInterface(t *testing.T) {\n\tg := NewGomegaWithT(t)\n\n\tvar _ Reconciler = (*AgentRuntimeReconciler)(nil)\n\tvar _ Reconciler = (*CodeInterpreterReconciler)(nil)\n\tg.Expect(true).To(BeTrue())\n}\n\nfunc TestControllerConfig(t *testing.T) {\n\tg := NewGomegaWithT(t)\n\n\tcfg := &ControllerConfig{\n\t\tRequeueAfter:          10 * time.Second,\n\t\tMaxConcurrentReconciles: 2,\n\t}\n\n\tg.Expect(cfg.RequeueAfter).To(Equal(10 * time.Second))\n\tg.Expect(cfg.MaxConcurrentReconciles).To(Equal(2))\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/ -run TestReconcilerInterface -v`\nExpected: FAIL with \"undefined: Reconciler\" and \"undefined: AgentRuntimeReconciler\"\n\n**Step 3: Write minimal implementation**\n\n```go\npackage reconciler\n\nimport (\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime\"\n)\n\n// Reconciler defines the interface for all reconcilers\ntype Reconciler interface {\n\tReconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error)\n\tSetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error\n}\n\n// ControllerConfig provides configuration for reconcilers\ntype ControllerConfig struct {\n\t// RequeueAfter is the default requeue interval\n\tRequeueAfter time.Duration\n\n\t// MaxConcurrentReconciles is the maximum number of concurrent reconciles\n\tMaxConcurrentReconciles int\n\n\t// SyncPeriod is the full resync period\n\tSyncPeriod *time.Duration\n\n\t// EnableLeaderElection enables leader election\n\tEnableLeaderElection bool\n\n\t// LeaderElectionID is the leader election ID\n\tLeaderElectionID string\n\n\t// LeaderElectionNamespace is the namespace for leader election\n\tLeaderElectionNamespace string\n\n\t// MetricsAddr is the metrics server address\n\tMetricsAddr string\n\n\t// EnableProfiling enables profiling endpoints\n\tEnableProfiling bool\n\n\t// ProbeAddr is the health probe address\n\tProbeAddr string\n}\n\n// AgentRuntimeReconciler reconciles AgentRuntime resources\ntype AgentRuntimeReconciler struct {\n\t// Implementation to be added in subsequent tasks\n}\n\n// CodeInterpreterReconciler reconciles CodeInterpreter resources\ntype CodeInterpreterReconciler struct {\n\t// Implementation to be added in subsequent tasks\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/ -run TestReconcilerInterface -v`\nExpected: PASS\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/types.go pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/types_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(ar-007): define reconciler types and interfaces\"\n```\n\n### Task 3: Define status condition types and constants\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/status.go`\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\n```go\n// pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/status_test.go\npackage reconciler\n\nimport (\n\t\"testing\"\n\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n\tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n)\n\nfunc TestConditionTypes(t *testing.T) {\n\tg := NewGomegaWithT(t)\n\n\tg.Expect(ConditionTypeReady).To(Equal(\"Ready\"))\n\tg.Expect(ConditionTypeAvailable).To(Equal(\"Available\"))\n\tg.Expect(ConditionTypeProgressing).To(Equal(\"Progressing\"))\n\tg.Expect(ConditionTypeError).To(Equal(\"Error\"))\n\tg.Expect(ConditionTypeSandboxCreated).To(Equal(\"SandboxCreated\"))\n}\n\nfunc TestReasonConstants(t *testing.T) {\n\tg := NewGomegaWithT(t)\n\n\tg.Expect(ReasonReconciliationStarted).To(Equal(\"ReconciliationStarted\"))\n\tg.Expect(ReasonSandboxCreated).To(Equal(\"SandboxCreated\"))\n\tg.Expect(ReasonValidationFailed).To(Equal(\"ValidationFailed\"))\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/ -run TestConditionTypes -v`\nExpected: FAIL with \"undefined: ConditionTypeReady\"\n\n**Step 3: Write minimal implementation**\n\n```go\npackage reconciler\n\nimport (\n\tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n)\n\n// Condition types for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter\nconst (\n\t// ConditionTypeReady indicates the resource is ready to serve requests\n\tConditionTypeReady = \"Ready\"\n\n\t// ConditionTypeAvailable indicates the runtime is available\n\tConditionTypeAvailable = \"Available\"\n\n\t// ConditionTypeProgressing indicates the resource is being reconciled\n\tConditionTypeProgressing = \"Progressing\"\n\n\t// ConditionTypeError indicates an error occurred during reconciliation\n\tConditionTypeError = \"Error\"\n\n\t// ConditionTypeSandboxCreated indicates the sandbox resource was created\n\tConditionTypeSandboxCreated = \"SandboxCreated\"\n)\n\n// Reason constants\nconst (\n\t// Reconciliation reasons\n\tReasonReconciliationStarted = \"ReconciliationStarted\"\n\tReasonReconciliationComplete = \"ReconciliationComplete\"\n\tReasonReconciliationFailed = \"ReconciliationFailed\"\n\n\t// Sandbox creation reasons\n\tReasonSandboxCreating = \"SandboxCreating\"\n\tReasonSandboxCreated = \"SandboxCreated\"\n\tReasonSandboxCreateFailed = \"SandboxCreateFailed\"\n\tReasonSandboxUpdating = \"SandboxUpdating\"\n\tReasonSandboxUpdated = \"SandboxUpdated\"\n\tReasonSandboxUpdateFailed = \"SandboxUpdateFailed\"\n\tReasonSandboxDeleting = \"SandboxDeleting\"\n\tReasonSandboxDeleted = \"SandboxDeleted\"\n\tReasonSandboxDeleteFailed = \"SandboxDeleteFailed\"\n\n\t// Validation reasons\n\tReasonValidationFailed = \"ValidationFailed\"\n\tReasonSpecInvalid = \"SpecInvalid\"\n\n\t// Cleanup reasons\n\tReasonCleanupFailed = \"CleanupFailed\"\n)\n\n// SetCondition sets a condition on the resource status\nfunc SetCondition(conditions *[]metav1.Condition, conditionType, reason, message string, status metav1.ConditionStatus, timestamp metav1.Time) {\n\t// Implementation in subsequent tasks\n}\n\n// GetCondition gets a condition of the specified type\nfunc GetCondition(conditions []metav1.Condition, conditionType string) *metav1.Condition {\n\t// Implementation in subsequent tasks\n\treturn nil\n}\n\n// IsReady returns true if the resource is ready\nfunc IsReady(conditions []metav1.Condition) bool {\n\t// Implementation in subsequent tasks\n\treturn false\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/ -run TestConditionTypes -v`\nExpected: PASS\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/status.go pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/status_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(ar-007): define status condition types and constants\"\n```\n\n### Task 4: Implement status condition management functions\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/status.go`\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\n```go\n// pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/status_test.go\nfunc TestSetCondition(t *testing.T) {\n\tg := NewGomegaWithT(t)\n\n\tvar conditions []metav1.Condition\n\tnow := metav1.Now()\n\n\tSetCondition(&conditions, ConditionTypeReady, \"ReadyReason\", \"Ready message\", metav1.ConditionTrue, now)\n\n\tg.Expect(conditions).To(HaveLen(1))\n\tg.Expect(conditions[0].Type).To(Equal(ConditionTypeReady))\n\tg.Expect(conditions[0].Status).To(Equal(metav1.ConditionTrue))\n\tg.Expect(conditions[0].Reason).To(Equal(\"ReadyReason\"))\n\tg.Expect(conditions[0].Message).To(Equal(\"Ready message\"))\n}\n\nfunc TestGetCondition(t *testing.T) {\n\tg := NewGomegaWithT(t)\n\n\tconditions := []metav1.Condition{\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tType:   ConditionTypeReady,\n\t\t\tStatus: metav1.ConditionTrue,\n\t\t},\n\t}\n\n\tcondition := GetCondition(conditions, ConditionTypeReady)\n\tg.Expect(condition).NotTo(BeNil())\n\tg.Expect(condition.Type).To(Equal(ConditionTypeReady))\n\n\tcondition = GetCondition(conditions, ConditionTypeError)\n\tg.Expect(condition).To(BeNil())\n}\n\nfunc TestIsReady(t *testing.T) {\n\tg := NewGomegaWithT(t)\n\n\tconditions := []metav1.Condition{\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tType:   ConditionTypeReady,\n\t\t\tStatus: metav1.ConditionTrue,\n\t\t},\n\t}\n\n\tg.Expect(IsReady(conditions)).To(BeTrue())\n\n\tconditions[0].Status = metav1.ConditionFalse\n\tg.Expect(IsReady(conditions)).To(BeFalse())\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/ -run TestSetCondition -v`\nExpected: FAIL with SetCondition not setting conditions correctly\n\n**Step 3: Write minimal implementation**\n\n```go\n// SetCondition sets a condition on the resource status\nfunc SetCondition(conditions *[]metav1.Condition, conditionType, reason, message string, status metav1.ConditionStatus, timestamp metav1.Time) {\n\t// Find existing condition\n\texistingIndex := -1\n\tfor i, c := range *conditions {\n\t\tif c.Type == conditionType {\n\t\t\texistingIndex = i\n\t\t\tbreak\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// Create new condition\n\tnewCondition := metav1.Condition{\n\t\tType:               conditionType,\n\t\tStatus:             status,\n\t\tReason:             reason,\n\t\tMessage:            message,\n\t\tLastTransitionTime: timestamp,\n\t}\n\n\t// Update or append\n\tif existingIndex >= 0 {\n\t\t// Only update transition time if status changed\n\t\tif (*conditions)[existingIndex].Status != status {\n\t\t\t(*conditions)[existingIndex].LastTransitionTime = timestamp\n\t\t}\n\t\t(*conditions)[existingIndex] = newCondition\n\t} else {\n\t\t*conditions = append(*conditions, newCondition)\n\t}\n}\n\n// GetCondition gets a condition of the specified type\nfunc GetCondition(conditions []metav1.Condition, conditionType string) *metav1.Condition {\n\tfor i := range conditions {\n\t\tif conditions[i].Type == conditionType {\n\t\t\treturn &conditions[i]\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn nil\n}\n\n// IsReady returns true if the resource is ready\nfunc IsReady(conditions []metav1.Condition) bool {\n\tcondition := GetCondition(conditions, ConditionTypeReady)\n\treturn condition != nil && condition.Status == metav1.ConditionTrue\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/ -run TestSetCondition -v`\nExpected: PASS\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/status.go pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/status_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(ar-007): implement status condition management functions\"\n```\n\n### Task 5: Define finalizer constants and utilities\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/finalizers.go`\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\n```go\n// pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/finalizers_test.go\npackage reconciler\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"testing\"\n\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n\tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/types\"\n\t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client\"\n\t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client/fake\"\n)\n\nfunc TestFinalizerConstants(t *testing.T) {\n\tg := NewGomegaWithT(t)\n\n\tg.Expect(FinalizerAgentRuntime).To(Equal(\"agentruntime.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/finalizer\"))\n\tg.Expect(FinalizerCodeInterpreter).To(Equal(\"codeinterpreter.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/finalizer\"))\n}\n\nfunc TestHasFinalizer(t *testing.T) {\n\tg := NewGomegaWithT(t)\n\n\tobj := &metav1.ObjectMeta{\n\t\tFinalizers: []string{\"finalizer1\", FinalizerAgentRuntime},\n\t}\n\n\tg.Expect(HasFinalizer(obj, FinalizerAgentRuntime)).To(BeTrue())\n\tg.Expect(HasFinalizer(obj, \"nonexistent\")).To(BeFalse())\n}\n\nfunc TestAddFinalizer(t *testing.T) {\n\tg := NewGomegaWithT(t)\n\n\tctx := context.Background()\n\tscheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n\n\tfakeClient := fake.NewClientBuilder().WithScheme(scheme).Build()\n\n\tobj := &metav1.ObjectMeta{\n\t\tName:       \"test\",\n\t\tFinalizers: []string{},\n\t}\n\n\terr := AddFinalizer(ctx, fakeClient, obj, FinalizerAgentRuntime)\n\tg.Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\tg.Expect(obj.Finalizers).To(ContainElement(FinalizerAgentRuntime))\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/ -run TestFinalizerConstants -v`\nExpected: FAIL with \"undefined: FinalizerAgentRuntime\"\n\n**Step 3: Write minimal implementation**\n\n```go\npackage reconciler\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\n\tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n\t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client\"\n)\n\nconst (\n\t// FinalizerAgentRuntime is the finalizer for AgentRuntime resources\n\tFinalizerAgentRuntime = \"agentruntime.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/finalizer\"\n\n\t// FinalizerCodeInterpreter is the finalizer for CodeInterpreter resources\n\tFinalizerCodeInterpreter = \"codeinterpreter.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/finalizer\"\n)\n\n// AddFinalizer adds a finalizer to the resource if not already present\nfunc AddFinalizer(ctx context.Context, client client.Client, obj client.Object, finalizer string) error {\n\tif !HasFinalizer(obj, finalizer) {\n\t\tobj.SetFinalizers(append(obj.GetFinalizers(), finalizer))\n\t\treturn client.Update(ctx, obj)\n\t}\n\treturn nil\n}\n\n// RemoveFinalizer removes a finalizer from the resource\nfunc RemoveFinalizer(ctx context.Context, client client.Client, obj client.Object, finalizer string) error {\n\tfinalizers := obj.GetFinalizers()\n\tnewFinalizers := []string{}\n\n\tfor _, f := range finalizers {\n\t\tif f != finalizer {\n\t\t\tnewFinalizers = append(newFinalizers, f)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tif len(newFinalizers) != len(finalizers) {\n\t\tobj.SetFinalizers(newFinalizers)\n\t\treturn client.Update(ctx, obj)\n\t}\n\n\treturn nil\n}\n\n// HasFinalizer checks if the resource has the specified finalizer\nfunc HasFinalizer(obj client.Object, finalizer string) bool {\n\tfor _, f := range obj.GetFinalizers() {\n\t\tif f == finalizer {\n\t\t\treturn true\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn false\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/ -run TestFinalizerConstants -v`\nExpected: PASS\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/finalizers.go pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/finalizers_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(ar-007): define finalizer constants and utilities\"\n```\n\n### Task 6: Define event predicates\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/predicates.go`\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\n```go\n// pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/predicates_test.go\npackage reconciler\n\nimport (\n\t\"testing\"\n\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n\t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/event\"\n\t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/predicate\"\n)\n\nfunc TestResourceGenerationChangedPredicate(t *testing.T) {\n\tg := NewGomegaWithT(t)\n\n\tp := &ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate{}\n\n\t// Test Create event - should pass\n\tcreateEvent := event.CreateEvent{}\n\tg.Expect(p.Create(createEvent)).To(BeTrue())\n\n\t// Test Delete event - should pass\n\tdeleteEvent := event.DeleteEvent{}\n\tg.Expect(p.Delete(deleteEvent)).To(BeTrue())\n\n\t// Test Update event with generation change - should pass\n\tupdateEvent := event.UpdateEvent{\n\t\tObjectOld: &metav1.ObjectMeta{Generation: 1},\n\t\tObjectNew: &metav1.ObjectMeta{Generation: 2},\n\t}\n\tg.Expect(p.Update(updateEvent)).To(BeTrue())\n\n\t// Test Update event without generation change - should fail\n\tupdateEventNoChange := event.UpdateEvent{\n\t\tObjectOld: &metav1.ObjectMeta{Generation: 1},\n\t\tObjectNew: &metav1.ObjectMeta{Generation: 1},\n\t}\n\tg.Expect(p.Update(updateEventNoChange)).To(BeFalse())\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/ -run TestResourceGenerationChangedPredicate -v`\nExpected: FAIL with \"undefined: ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate\"\n\n**Step 3: Write minimal implementation**\n\n```go\npackage reconciler\n\nimport (\n\t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/event\"\n\t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/predicate\"\n)\n\n// ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate filters events based on generation changes\ntype ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate struct {\n\tpredicate.Funcs\n}\n\n// Update implements default UpdateEvent filter for validating generation change\nfunc (p ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate) Update(e event.UpdateEvent) bool {\n\tif e.ObjectOld == nil {\n\t\treturn false\n\t}\n\tif e.ObjectNew == nil {\n\t\treturn false\n\t}\n\treturn e.ObjectNew.GetGeneration() != e.ObjectOld.GetGeneration()\n}\n\n// SetupWithManager registers the predicate with the controller\nfunc (p *ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error {\n\treturn nil\n}\n\n// LabelChangedPredicate filters events based on label changes\ntype LabelChangedPredicate struct {\n\tpredicate.Funcs\n}\n\n// AnnotationChangedPredicate filters events based on annotation changes\ntype AnnotationChangedPredicate struct {\n\tpredicate.Funcs\n}\n\n// PauseAnnotationPredicate filters events for