un: `go doc ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/...`\n\n**Step 4: Final commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add .\ngit commit -m \"feat(ar-007): complete K8s Reconciler controller implementation\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThis implementation plan breaks down AR-007 into 25 atomic, independently verifiable tasks following TDD principles. Each task includes:\n\n1. **Failing test** first (Red)\n2. **Minimal implementation** to make test pass (Green)\n3. **Test verification** to confirm it passes\n4. **Commit** to save progress\n\nThe plan covers all acceptance criteria from the design document and ensures:\n- Reconciler structure and interfaces are properly defined\n- Status condition management is implemented\n- Finalizer handling is correct\n- Event predicates filter unnecessary reconciles\n- Metrics are exposed for monitoring\n- Both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter reconcilers are implemented\n- Sandbox lifecycle management is complete\n- RBAC permissions are defined\n- Examples and documentation are provided\n- Unit and integration tests validate functionality\n- Error handling is robust\n\nEach step can be completed in 2-5 minutes and committed frequently, providing clear progress indicators and the ability to roll back if needed.","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/tasks.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/controller/sandbox.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":90,"character":5},"end":{"line":90,"character":24}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#rangeint"},"source":"rangeint","message":"for loop can be modernized using range over int"},{"range":{"start":{"line":155,"character":12},"end":{"line":155,"character":23}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"